INSERT INTO `Directions` (RecipeID, SortOrder, Direction) VALUES ('26903', '3', 'Broil 3 inches from heat 2 to 3 minutes or just until cheese starts to brown.'),
('26905', '1', 'Heat 1/3 cup of the olive oil in a soup pot.'),
('26905', '2', 'Add the onion, garlic and a large pinch of salt and cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, until the onion is softened, about 5 minutes. Stir in the cumin and cook until fragrant, about 1 minute.'),
('26905', '3', 'Add the tomatoes and bring to a boil. Cook over moderate heat, stirring occasionally, until the tomatoes are soupy, about 20 minutes.'),
('26905', '4', 'Pass the soup through a food mill or fine sieve, pressing hard on the solids. Return the soup to the pot.'),
('26905', '5', 'Add the chicken stock and sugar and season with salt and pepper. Simmer over moderate heat until reduced to 10 cups, about 25 minutes. Stir in the parsley and chopped lovage. Ladle the soup into shallow bowls, garnish with the lovage leaves and drizzle with olive oil.'),
('26905', '6', 'Serve hot.'),
('26906', '1', 'In a large soup pot, heat the olive oil.'),
('26906', '2', 'Add the onion, fennel and thyme and cook the vegetables over moderately high heat, stirring occasionally, until the onion and fennel are softened, about 8 minutes. Stir in the tomato paste and season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring, for 5 minutes.'),
('26906', '3', 'Add the water and the tomatoes and their juices and bring to a boil. Simmer the soup over moderate heat, stirring occasionally, until the liquid is reduced by one-third, about 30 minutes. Discard the thyme.'),
('26906', '4', 'Transfer half of the soup to a blender and puree until smooth. Return the puree to the pot.'),
('26906', '5', 'Serve the soup with Pan-Fried Potato Croutons, Fennel-Orange Gremolata and diced Fontina cheese.'),
('26907', '1', 'Preheat the oven to 325 and position 2 racks just above and just below the middle of the oven. Working over a medium bowl, pry the seeds and pulp out of the tomatoes and discard.'),
('26907', '2', 'Pour 1/4 cup of the olive oil onto each of 2 very sturdy, rimmed, light-colored baking sheets. Arrange the tomatoes cut side down on the baking sheets and scatter the garlic and thyme all around. Make a tiny slit on each tomato.'),
('26907', '3', 'Bake the tomatoes for about 45 minutes, until the skins begin to wrinkle. Shift the pans from top to bottom halfway through. Carefully pinch off the skins. Flip each tomato and bake until the surface looks dry, about 1 hour. Flip the tomatoes again and continue baking until the surfaces look dry but the tomatoes are still slightly plump, about 2 hours longer. Season the tomatoes with salt and pepper and let cool completely.'),
('26907', '4', 'Discard the thyme sprigs and peel the garlic cloves. Layer the tomatoes with the garlic in five 1/2-pint jars.'),
('26907', '5', 'Add enough olive oil to cover the tomatoes by at least 1 inch. Slide the blade of a knife along the side of each jar to release any air bubbles. Seal the jars and refrigerate for up to 2 months or freeze for up to 6 months.'),
('26908', '1', 'Light a grill. Arrange four 12-by-24-inch sheets of heavy-duty foil on a work surface. Mound the tomatoes in the center of each sheet, drizzle with the olive oil and season with salt and pepper. Fold up the foil to create tight packets.'),
('26908', '2', 'Set the packets on the grill and cover. Grill over moderately high heat for about 18 minutes, until the tomatoes begin to soften and burst. Using scissors, carefully cut open the foil packets and serve.'),
('26917', '1', 'Combine first 6 ingredients in a large saucepan. bring to a boil. Reduce heat, and simmer 30 minutes.'),
('26917', '2', 'Place half of tomato mixture in a blender.'),
('26917', '3', 'Remove center piece of blender lid (to allow steam to escape). secure blender lid on blender.'),
('26917', '4', 'Place a clean towel over opening in blender lid (to avoid splatters). Blend until smooth.'),
('26917', '5', 'Pour into a large bowl. Repeat procedure with remaining tomato mixture. Stir in salt and pepper. Ladle 3/4 cup soup into each of 6 bowls. top each serving with 1 tablespoon yogurt and 1 1/2 teaspoons basil.'),
('26918', '1', 'Preheat broiler.'),
('26918', '2', 'Core tomatoes, and halve crosswise. Working with 1 tomato at a time, squeeze tomato halves over a sieve over a bowl. press sieve gently with the back of a wooden spoon to extract remaining juice, reserving tomato halves and juice. Discard seeds.'),
('26918', '3', 'Press tomato halves through large holes of a box grater into a large bowl. discard skins.'),
('26918', '4', 'Add reserved tomato juice to bowl. Stir in 2 tablespoons chopped mint, 1/2 teaspoon salt, and vinegar.'),
('26918', '5', 'Place garlic in a food processor. process until chopped.'),
('26918', '6', 'Add 1/2 cup mint leaves and 1/8 teaspoon salt. process until pureed. With the motor running, gradually pour oil through food chute, processing until oil is fully incorporated, scraping sides as necessary.'),
('26918', '7', 'Slice bread crosswise into 8 slices.'),
('26918', '8', 'Spread cream cheese evenly over 1 side of bread slices.'),
('26918', '9', 'Place bread, cheese side up, in a single layer on a baking sheet. Broil 2 minutes or until golden. Ladle about 1 cup soup into each of 4 bowls. divide pesto evenly among bowls.'),
('26918', '10', 'Serve with toasts.'),
('26919', '1', 'Combine all ingredients in a large saucepan. bring to a boil. Reduce heat, and simmer, uncovered, 45 minutes or until thick (B), stirring frequently. Cool. pour into airtight containers.'),
('26919', '2', 'Note: Refrigerate Red Tomato Chutney in airtight containers up to two months.'),
('26920', '1', 'Bring 2 qt. water to a boil in a Dutch oven. add shrimp, and cook 3 to 5 minutes or just until shrimp turn pink.'),
('26920', '2', 'Drain and rinse with cold water.'),
('26920', '3', 'Whisk together egg and buttermilk in a shallow bowl or pie plate.'),
('26920', '4', 'Combine cornmeal, 1 teaspoon salt, 1/2 teaspoon pepper, and 1/4 cup flour in another shallow bowl or pie plate.'),
('26920', '5', 'Dredge tomato slices in remaining 1/4 cup flour. dip in egg mixture, and dredge in cornmeal mixture.'),
('26920', '6', 'Pour oil to a depth of 1/2 inch in a large cast-iron skillet. heat to 37'),
('26920', '7', 'Fry tomatoes, in batches, in hot oil 2 minutes on each side or until golden.'),
('26920', '8', 'Drain on paper towels or a wire rack. Sprinkle hot tomatoes with salt to taste.'),
('26920', '9', 'Arrange tomatoes on a serving plate. Spoon 2 tablespoons Rmoulade Sauce on center of each tomato. Top each with 3 shrimp.'),
('26920', '10', 'Serve immediately.'),
('26920', '11', 'Garnish, if desired.'),
('26924', '1', 'In a medium saucepan, bring the vinegar, brown sugar and salt to a boil, stirring.'),
('26924', '2', 'Remove from the heat.'),
('26924', '3', 'In a medium skillet, heat the oil.'),
('26924', '4', 'Add the garlic, grated ginger, mustard seeds, black pepper, turmeric, ground cumin and cayenne pepper and cook over low heat until fragrant, about 2 minutes. Carefully pour the hot oil into the vinegar mixture.'),
('26924', '5', 'In a large heatproof bowl, combine the tomatoes, scallions and jalapeos. Stir in the hot pickling liquid and let stand at room temperature for 4 hours or refrigerate for 8 hours, then serve.'),
('26928', '1', 'Place 2 to 3 Fried Green Tomatoes on individual serving plates, and top each with 1 1/2 Tbsp. Rmoulade Sauce and 3 shrimp.'),
('26928', '2', 'Garnish with fresh pea shoots or arugula, if desired.'),
('26930', '1', 'Preheat oven to 20'),
('26930', '2', 'Combine first 7 ingredients in a large bowl, tossing gently to coat. Arrange tomatoes, cut side up, on a baking sheet coated with cooking spray. Roast at 200 for 7 1/2 hours.'),
('26938', '1', 'Combine tomato, 1/2 teaspoon salt, and next 7 ingredients in a large bowl. set aside.'),
('26938', '2', 'Sprinkle salmon with pepper and remaining 1/4 teaspoon salt.'),
('26938', '3', 'Heat oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat.'),
('26938', '4', 'Add salmon. cook 3 to 5 minutes or until golden on both sides but not cooked through, turning once.'),
('26938', '5', 'Transfer fish to a plate.'),
('26938', '6', 'Add onion to skillet. cook 3 minutes, stirring constantly. Stir in tomato mixture. cook for 4 minutes or until liquid begins to thicken, stirring constantly. Gently place salmon on top of tomato mixture. Cook 2 to 3 minutes or until desired degree of doneness. Sprinkle with mint.'),
('26938', '7', 'Serve with hot cooked couscous.'),
('26938', '8', '*The green pitted salad olives (not to be confused with pimiento-stuffed Spanish olives) have a similar flavor to--and may be substituted with--ripe black olives.'),
('26944', '1', 'Saut onions in 2 Tbsp. hot oil in a large Dutch oven over medium-high heat 9 to 10 minutes or until tender.'),
('26944', '2', 'Add tomatoes and chicken broth. Bring to a boil, reduce heat to medium-low, and simmer, stirring occasionally, 20 minutes. Process mixture with a handheld blender until smooth.'),
('26944', '3', 'Process basil, next 4 ingredients, 1/4 cup water, and remaining 2 Tbsp. oil in a food processor until smooth, stopping to scrape down sides. Stir basil mixture, sugar, and pepper into soup. Cook 10 minutes or until thoroughly heated.'),
('26944', '4', 'Meanwhile, cook okra according to package directions.'),
('26944', '5', 'Serve with soup.'),
('26948', '1', 'Watch how to make this recipe.'),
('26948', '2', 'In a large bowl, combine the cornmeal, flour, garlic powder, and cayenne together.'),
('26948', '3', 'Pour the buttermilk into a separate bowl and season with salt and pepper. Dip the tomatoes in the buttermilk and then dredge them in the cornmeal mixture, coating both sides well.'),
('26948', '4', 'Place a large cast iron skillet over medium heat and coat with the oil. When the oil is hot, pan-fry the tomatoes (in batches if necessary) until golden brown and crispy on both sides, about 3 to 4 minutes on each side. Carefully remove the tomatoes and drain on paper towels.'),
('26948', '5', 'Serve with hot pepper sauce and lemon.'),
('26949', '1', 'Preheat oven to 40'),
('26949', '2', 'Combine 1 pound trimmed asparagus, 1/2 cup cherry or grape tomatoes, 1/3 cup sliced shallots, 1 1/2 teaspoons chopped fresh thyme, 1/4 teaspoon salt, and 1/4 teaspoon pepper on a jelly-roll pan. Coat lightly with cooking spray.'),
('26949', '3', 'Bake at 400 for 6 minutes or until crisp-tender.'),
('26952', '1', 'Preheat oven to 42'),
('26952', '2', 'Combine 1 cup halved cherry tomatoes, 1 tablespoon olive oil, 1 sliced garlic clove, 1/4 teaspoon salt, 1/2 teaspoon black pepper, and 1/4 cup fresh basil leaves. roast in middle of oven until tomatoes wilt and are golden (about 20 minutes).'),
('26952', '3', 'Remove from oven. drizzle with 2 teaspoons balsamic vinegar. Roast an additional 10 minutes.'),
('26952', '4', 'Spread 1/4 cup packaged herbed goat cheese evenly onto 12 toasted crostini. top with tomato mixture.'),
('26953', '1', 'Watch how to make this recipe.'),
('26953', '2', 'Combine the vinegar, sugar, ginger, dry mustard, turmeric, mustard seeds, celery seeds, pickling spice and 1 teaspoon salt in a large pot. Bring to a boil over high heat, then reduce the heat and simmer 15 minutes to extract the flavors of the spices.'),
('26953', '3', 'Return to high heat. once the mixture is boiling and steaming, add the tomatoes and onions, stirring to coat everything evenly. Reduce the heat and simmer 5 minutes.'),
('26953', '4', 'Remove from the heat and cool to room temperature.'),
('26953', '5', 'Photographs by James Baigrie'),
('26954', '1', 'Watch how to make this recipe.'),
('26954', '2', 'Preheat the oven to 275 degrees F. Line a baking sheet with parchment paper.'),
('26954', '3', 'In a bowl, toss the tomatoes with 1 tablespoon olive oil, salt, and pepper.'),
('26954', '4', 'Place the tomatoes, cut side down, on the prepared baking sheet and drizzle 1 tablespoon water over the tomatoes.'),
('26954', '5', 'Bake in the oven for 1 hour.'),
('26954', '6', 'Remove from the oven. Carefully peel off the skins and discard. Flip the tomatoes over so they''re cut side up, and place back in the oven until the tomatoes are shriveled but not dry, another 30 to 60 minutes.'),
('26954', '7', 'Remove the tomatoes from the oven and allow to cool slightly.'),
('26954', '8', 'Meanwhile, in a large saucepan, saute the onion in the remaining 1 tablespoon olive oil over low heat until very soft, 10 to 12 minutes.'),
('26954', '9', 'Add the garlic and herbes de provence and cook until fragrant, another 1 to 2 minutes.'),
('26954', '10', 'Add the stock and remaining 1/2 cup water and bring to a simmer. Simmer 15 minutes. Cool slightly.'),
('26954', '11', 'In a blender, puree the tomatoes (including any cooking liquid on the baking sheet) and the stock mixture until very smooth. You may need to work in batches. Strain through a fine sieve if a very smooth texture is desired.'),
('26954', '12', 'Pour the soup back into the saucepan, season with salt and pepper, and heat gently. To serve, ladle into cups or bowls and top with either a swirl of olive oil or a little sour cream, if desired.'),
('26956', '1', 'Combine first 4 ingredients in a bowl, stirring well. Arrange tomatoes on a platter. Sprinkle tomatoes evenly with salt and pepper. drizzle with shallot mixture.'),
('26960', '1', 'Heat a large nonstick skillet coated with cooking spray over medium-high heat.'),
('26960', '2', 'Add bell pepper and shrimp. saute 7 minutes or until shrimp are done.'),
('26960', '3', 'Add tomato and onions. cook 3 minutes, stirring frequently.'),
('26960', '4', 'Remove from heat. keep warm.'),
('26960', '5', 'Bring milk and broth to a boil in a large saucepan over medium-high heat. gradually stir in grits. Cover, reduce heat to low, and simmer 5 minutes or until thick, stirring occasionally.'),
('26960', '6', 'Add cheese and Worcestershire, stirring until cheese melts.'),
('26960', '7', 'Serve shrimp mixture over grits.'),
('26964', '1', 'Heat the olive oil in a saute pan large enough to hold all the tomatoes in one layer.'),
('26964', '2', 'Add the garlic to the oil and cook over medium heat for 30 seconds.'),
('26964', '3', 'Add the tomatoes, basil, parsley, thyme, salt, and pepper. Reduce the heat to low and cook for 5 to 7 minutes, tossing occasionally, until the tomatoes begin to loose their firm round shape. Sprinkle with a little fresh chopped basil and parsley and serve hot or at room temperature.'),
('26965', '1', 'Cut the tomatoes in half crosswise, season with House Seasoning.'),
('26965', '2', 'Heat the oil in a small frying pan over medium heat.'),
('26965', '3', 'Add the garlic, and cook until just starting to turn golden brown, 1 to 2 minutes.'),
('26965', '4', 'Pour the garlic and oil into a heatproof bowl.'),
('26965', '5', 'Oil the grill and set for high heat.'),
('26965', '6', 'Place the tomatoes cut side down and grill for 3 to 5 minutes. Turn over, top with the garlic oil mixture and continue to cook for another 3 minutes.'),
('26965', '7', 'Remove from grill and top with thyme, House Seasoning and Parmigiano-Reggiano.'),
('26965', '8', 'Serve immediately.'),
('26965', '9', 'Mix ingredients together and store in an airtight container for up to 6 months.'),
('26971', '1', 'Combine first 5 ingredients in a large saucepan. bring to a boil. Cover, reduce heat, and simmer 10 minutes. Partially mash tomatoes and beans with a potato masher. Stir in chicken. cook 2 minutes or until thoroughly heated.'),
('26971', '2', 'Remove from heat. stir in oil.'),
('26971', '3', 'Place 1 1/4 cups soup in each of four bowls. Top each serving with 2 tablespoons sour cream and 1 tablespoon cilantro.'),
('26973', '1', 'Heat oil in a Dutch oven over medium heat. add onion and garlic and saut until onion is translucent.'),
('26973', '2', 'Add celery and carrot. cook 5 more minutes.'),
('26973', '3', 'Add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil. Reduce heat. cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours or until thickened. Ladle soup into 4 bowls. top each serving evenly with Italian Croutons.'),
('26974', '1', 'Fill a large pitcher with the ice.'),
('26974', '2', 'Combine the vegetable juice, horseradish, okra juice, olive juice, hot sauce and vodka. Season with smoked salt and pepper. Fill 4 glasses with the juice.'),
('26974', '3', 'Garnish with a dash of hot sauce, 1 celery stick, some green olives, 1 piece of pickled okra and some chives. Sprinkle with smoked salt, if desired.'),
('26974', '4', 'Serve immediately.'),
('26977', '1', 'Preheat oven to 20'),
('26977', '2', 'Place a wire rack over a baking sheet. set aside.'),
('26977', '3', 'Combine tomatoes, 1 tablespoon oil, and vinegar. toss gently.'),
('26977', '4', 'Place tomatoes, cut sides up, on rack. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.'),
('26977', '5', 'Bake at 200 for 6 hours or until tender and slightly syrupy (do not overbake or tomatoes will be tough and chewy).'),
('26977', '6', 'Remove from oven. cool completely.'),
('26977', '7', 'Place 1/2 teaspoon cheese onto each tomato half. Fold slightly. secure each tomato half with 1 rosemary sprig.'),
('26977', '8', 'Place on a serving platter. drizzle with the remaining 1 tablespoon oil.'),
('26979', '1', 'Combine first 6 ingredients in a large saucepan. bring to a boil. Reduce heat, and simmer 30 minutes.'),
('26979', '2', 'Place half of tomato mixture in a blender.'),
('26979', '3', 'Remove center piece of blender lid (to allow steam to escape). secure blender lid on blender.'),
('26979', '4', 'Place a clean towel over opening in blender lid (to avoid splatters). Blend until smooth.'),
('26979', '5', 'Pour into a large bowl. Repeat procedure with remaining tomato mixture. Stir in salt and pepper. Ladle 3/4 cup soup into each of 6 bowls. top each serving with 1 tablespoon yogurt and 1 1/2 teaspoons basil.'),
('26984', '1', 'Whisk together egg and buttermilk in a medium bowl.'),
('26984', '2', 'Combine cornmeal, salt, and pepper in a shallow dish. Dip tomato slices in egg mixture, then coat with seasoned cornmeal.'),
('26984', '3', 'Heat oil in a large saut pan over medium heat.'),
('26984', '4', 'Place tomato slices in pan in a single layer, and cook until golden brown on bottom, about 3 minutes. Flip and brown other side, about 3 minutes more. Interior should be cooked through but not mushy.'),
('26984', '5', 'Place 2 tomato slices on each of 4 serving plates and top each slice with 3 shrimp. Spoon 1 1/2 tablespoons Remoulade Sauce over each slice, and garnish, if desired.'),
('26984', '6', 'Serve immediately.'),
('26989', '1', 'Whisk together balsamic vinegar, minced garlic, brown sugar, olive oil, and salt. Stir in diced peach and chopped fresh basil. Spoon over sliced heirloom tomatoes. top with crumbled goat cheese and chopped toasted pecans. Sprinkle with freshly ground pepper to taste.'),
('26990', '1', 'Prepare grill to medium-high heat.'),
('26990', '2', 'Arrange bell peppers, skin side down, and corn in a single layer on a grill rack. grill 5 minutes, turning corn occasionally.'),
('26990', '3', 'Add tomatoes. grill an additional 5 minutes or until vegetables are slightly charred.'),
('26990', '4', 'Remove from heat. cool 10 minutes. Coarsely chop tomatoes and bell peppers. place in a medium bowl.'),
('26990', '5', 'Cut kernels from ears of corn. add to tomato mixture.'),
('26990', '6', 'Heat oil in a large Dutch oven over medium heat.'),
('26990', '7', 'Add onion. cook 7 minutes or until tender, stirring occasionally. Stir in tomato mixture. cook 3 minutes, stirring occasionally. Increase heat to high, and stir in broth. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat, and simmer 30 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Cool 20 minutes.'),
('26990', '8', 'Place one-third of tomato mixture in a blender. process until smooth.'),
('26990', '9', 'Place pureed mixture in a large bowl. Repeat procedure twice with remaining tomato mixture. Wipe pan clean with paper towels. Press tomato mixture through a sieve into pan. discard solids.'),
('26990', '10', 'Place pan over medium heat. cook until thoroughly heated. Stir in salt and black pepper. Ladle about 1 1/2 cups soup into each of 6 bowls. top each serving with 2 teaspoons cheese and 1 teaspoon chives.'),
('26991', '1', 'In a medium saucepan, combine the tomatoes with the olive oil, basil, garlic, vinegar and sugar. Season with salt and pepper. Cook over low heat until hot but not boiling, about 10 minutes. Pass the soup through the fine disk of a food mill into a medium bowl to remove the tomato seeds and skin. Chill the soup in the refrigerator or quick-chill it by setting the bowl in a larger bowl of ice water.'),
('26991', '2', 'Using a small melon baller, scoop a total of 20 balls from the cucumber and melons. Alternatively, cut the cucumber and melons into 1/2-inch dice.'),
('26991', '3', 'Pour the soup into bowls.'),
('26991', '4', 'Garnish with the melon and cucumber balls and the basil sprigs and serve.'),
('26993', '1', 'Preheat the oven to 35'),
('26993', '2', 'Spread the pine nuts in a pie plate and bake for 10 minutes, or until fragrant and lightly toasted.'),
('26993', '3', 'Transfer to a plate and let cool.'),
('26993', '4', 'In a standing mixer, using the paddle, blend the goat cheese with the toasted pine nuts, rosemary, thyme and piment d''Espelette. Alternatively, blend the cheese in a bowl using a wooden spoon. Season with salt. Shape rounded tablespoons of the seasoned cheese into balls.'),
('26993', '5', 'Pour 1 inch of olive oil into a tall 1-gallon glass container. Layer the cheese balls, artichoke hearts, cherry tomatoes and olives in the container with enough of the remaining olive oil to cover.'),
('26993', '6', 'Let marinate at room temperature for 24 hours.'),
('26993', '7', 'Serve with the toasted baguette.'),
('26996', '1', 'Watch how to make this recipe.'),
('26996', '2', 'Preheat the oven to 425 degrees F.'),
('26996', '3', 'Put the prepared vegetables and the garlic on a baking sheet and drizzle them with olive oil. Season them with 1 teaspoon salt and 1 teaspoon freshly cracked black pepper. Roast them until the vegetables have begun to brown, about 15 to 20 minutes.'),
('26996', '4', 'Remove them from the oven and set aside.'),
('26996', '5', 'Start preparing a roux in the Dutch oven by melting the butter over medium-high heat.'),
('26996', '6', 'Add the flour and stir constantly for 5 minutes. Immediately add the vegetable mixture and any extra juices to the roux. Stir until incorporated. Season with the cumin and remaining salt and pepper. Reduce the heat and simmer for 30 minutes.'),
('26996', '7', 'Stir the cilantro and cream into the vegetable mixture and warm it over low heat. Adjust the seasoning, if necessary.'),
('26996', '8', 'Transfer the soup to a serving bowl and enjoy! (Chefs Note: Do not return to a boil once the cream has been incorporated.)'),
('26999', '1', 'Slice the tomatoes 1/4-inch thick. Lay them out in a shallow baking pan and sprinkle with salt.'),
('26999', '2', 'Place the tomato slices in a colander and allow time for salt to pull the water out of the tomatoes, approximately 30 minutes.'),
('26999', '3', 'In a skillet, heat the oil for deep-frying over medium-high heat.'),
('26999', '4', 'Dip the tomatoes into buttermilk, then dredge them into flour with a dash of pepper. Deep-fry until golden brown. Keep warm.'),
('27002', '1', 'Prepare the'),
('27002', '2', 'Garnish: In a bowl, toss the celery with the onion, tomato, lemon zest and juice and season with salt. Refrigerate while you make the drinks.'),
('27002', '3', 'Make the Bloody Mary: In a blender, puree the tomatoes, vodka, ice, tomato paste, chile and celery salt. pour into glasses. Spoon the garnish on top, add a celery rib and chile to each glass and serve.'),
('27009', '1', 'Cook bacon slightly.'),
('27009', '2', 'Saute onion and garlic with bacon until tender.'),
('27009', '3', 'Add tomatoes, chicken base, sugar and pepper. Stir well and let simmer for about 20 minutes. Adjust seasoning if needed. Meanwhile wash okra and remove fuzz if using fresh and cut into pieces.'),
('27009', '4', 'Add the okra and simmer until okra is done, about 20 more minutes (less if using frozen okra).'),
('27013', '1', 'Heat olive oil in a large saucepan over medium heat.'),
('27013', '2', 'Add the onion, oregano, thyme, and garlic. cook 4 minutes, stirring frequently. Stir in tomato and next 5 ingredients (tomato through pepper). Bring to a boil. Reduce heat. simmer 15 minutes.'),
('27013', '3', 'Place half of soup in a blender or food processor. process until smooth, and pour into a bowl. Repeat procedure with the remaining soup.'),
('27013', '4', 'Serve warm or chilled. Sprinkle with fresh basil, if desired.'),
('27018', '1', 'In a soup pot, melt the butter in the olive oil.'),
('27018', '2', 'Add the onion and garlic and cook over moderately high heat until tender, about  5 minutes.'),
('27018', '3', 'Add the paprika and cook until fragrant, about 30 seconds.'),
('27018', '4', 'Add the tomatoes, water, thyme sprig and bay leaf, season with salt and pepper and bring the tomato mixture to a boil. Cover and simmer over moderate heat until the tomatoes break down, about 15 minutes. Discard the thyme sprig and bay leaf.'),
('27018', '5', 'Preheat the broiler. In a blender, puree the soup in batches until smooth. Strain the soup back into the pot, pressing on the solids to extract as much soup as possible. Stir the cream into the soup and season with salt and pepper.'),
('27018', '6', 'Meanwhile, place the baguette slices on a baking sheet. Broil 6 inches from the heat until lightly toasted on both sides, about 2 minutes total. Top the toasts with the Gruyre and broil for about 30 seconds, until the cheese is bubbly. Ladle the soup into bowls and serve with the Gruyre toasts.'),
('27027', '1', 'Prepare barbecue (medium heat).'),
('27027', '2', 'Brush corn and onion with oil. sprinkle lightly with salt and pepper.'),
('27027', '3', 'Place corn, onion halves, and tomatoes on grill. Cook until corn is charred, onion is just tender, and tomato skins are blistered and loose, turning often, about 12 minutes for tomatoes and 15 minutes for corn and onion.'),
('27027', '4', 'Transfer to foil-lined baking sheet and cool.'),
('27027', '5', 'Brush bread with oil. sprinkle with salt and pepper. Grill until crisp, about 2 minutes per side. Core tomatoes and cut in half horizontally. Gently squeeze out or spoon out juices and seeds. Coarsely dice tomato flesh and place in medium bowl.'),
('27027', '6', 'Cut corn kernels from cob. add kernels to tomatoes. Chop onion. add to tomatoes.'),
('27027', '7', 'Mix in garlic, lime juice, paprika, and 1 tablespoon oil. Season to taste with salt and pepper. DO AHEAD Can be made 3 hours ahead. Cover. let stand at room temperature.'),
('27027', '8', 'Serve with grilled bread.'),
('27029', '1', 'Sprinkle the tomato slices with the salt and pepper. set aside.'),
('27029', '2', 'Combine the cornmeal and paprika in a shallow bowl. In another bowl, beat the eggs.'),
('27029', '3', 'Cover the bottom of a heavy skillet with 1/2 inch of oil, then place it over medium-high heat.'),
('27029', '4', 'Coat the tomato slices in the egg, then dredge them in the cornmeal mixture.'),
('27029', '5', 'Fry as many tomatoes as fit comfortably in the pan until nicely browned, about 2 minutes a side.'),
('27029', '6', 'Transfer them to a paper towel-lined platter. Repeat until all the tomatoes are cooked.'),
('27033', '1', 'Combine halved tomatoes, finely chopped onion, 3 tablespoons olive oil, chopped fresh basil, and balsamic vinegar in medium bowl. season tomato topping with salt and pepper. DO AHEAD: Topping can be made 2 hours ahead. Cover and let stand at room temperature, tossing occasionally.'),
('27033', '2', 'Preheat broiler.'),
('27033', '3', 'Place focaccia half, cut side up, on baking sheet. brush bread with olive oil. Toast bread in broiler until top is golden brown, watching closely to avoid burning, about 2 minutes. Immediately rub cut side of bread all over with halved garlic, then cut focaccia crosswise into 4 equal pieces.'),
('27033', '4', 'Top toasted focaccia with tomato mixture and serve.'),
('27034', '1', 'Watch how to make this recipe.'),
('27037', '1', 'Heat olive oil in a 12-inch heavy-bottomed stainless steel saute pan over medium-high heat until shimmering.'),
('27037', '2', 'Add garlic and cooking, stirring occasionally, until fragrant, about 1 minute.'),
('27037', '3', 'Add tomatoes, season with salt and pepper, and cook, stirring occasionally, until they begin to break down, about 5 minutes.'),
('27037', '4', 'Add okra, cover, and cook, stirring and shaking the pan occasionally, until okra is cooked through, about 10 minutes. If pan runs dry, add up to 1/4 cup water to moisten. Season to taste with salt and pepper, and serve immediately.'),
('27039', '1', 'Heat olive oil in a large Dutch oven over medium-high heat.'),
('27039', '2', 'Add the onion. saut for 3 minutes or until tender.'),
('27039', '3', 'Add the turmeric and the next 6 ingredients (turmeric through garlic). saut for 1 minute.'),
('27039', '4', 'Add water and next 4 ingredients (water through diced tomatoes). bring to a boil. Reduce heat. simmer 1 hour.'),
('27039', '5', 'Reserve 2 cups lentil mixture.'),
('27039', '6', 'Place half of remaining mixture in blender. process until smooth.'),
('27039', '7', 'Pour pureed soup into a large bowl. Repeat procedure with other half of remaining mixture. Stir in reserved 2 cups lentil mixture.'),
('27039', '8', 'Garnish with chopped tomatoes and a cilantro sprig, if desired.'),
('27040', '1', 'Place tomatoes and boiling water in a bowl. Cover and let stand 30 minutes or until tender. drain and chop.'),
('27040', '2', 'While tomatoes steep, cook pasta according to package directions, omitting salt and fat.'),
('27040', '3', 'Drain.'),
('27040', '4', 'Steam broccoli, covered, 4 minutes or until crisp-tender. Set aside.'),
('27040', '5', 'Heat a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat. Coat pan with cooking spray.'),
('27040', '6', 'Add garlic to pan. saut 30 seconds.'),
('27040', '7', 'Add shrimp. cook 4 minutes.'),
('27040', '8', 'Add broth and cream cheese, stirring to combine. bring to a boil. Reduce heat, and simmer 2 minutes.'),
('27040', '9', 'Add tomatoes, broccoli, and basil. stir well. Cook 2 minutes or until thoroughly heated, stirring frequently.'),
('27040', '10', 'Remove from heat. Stir in pasta, Parmesan cheese, and juice.'),
('27040', '11', 'Serve immediately.'),
('27044', '1', 'Heat 1 tablespoon olive oil in mediumsaucepan over medium-high heat.'),
('27044', '2', 'Addonion. saute 4 to 5 minutes.'),
('27044', '3', 'Add garlic, bayleaf, and 1/2 teaspoon thyme. stir 1 minute.'),
('27044', '4', 'Add peas and broth. bring to boil. Coverwith lid slightly ajar. reduce heat to medium-low.Simmer until peas are soft, stirringoccasionally, about 25 minutes.'),
('27044', '5', 'Drain.'),
('27044', '6', 'Transfer to large microwave-safe bowl.'),
('27044', '7', 'Whisk vinegar and 1/4 cup extra-virginolive oil in bowl. Season with salt and pepper.'),
('27044', '8', 'Pour over warm peas. toss. DO AHEAD:  Can bemade 2 days ahead. Cover and chill. Bring toroom temperature before continuing.'),
('27044', '9', 'Stir basil into peas. Discard bay leaf.Season to taste with salt and pepper.'),
('27044', '10', 'Arrange tomato slices on platter.Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Spoon warmor room-temperature peas over tomatoes.'),
('27046', '1', 'Combine first 3 ingredients in a cocktail shaker. Press leaves against bottom of cup using a muddler or wooden spoon to release flavors. stir in tomato juice and next 7 ingredients.'),
('27046', '2', 'Transfer half of mixture to a 2-cup glass measuring cup.'),
('27046', '3', 'Place ice in cocktail shaker, filling halfway full. Cover with lid, and shake vigorously until thoroughly chilled. Strain into a glass over ice. Repeat procedure with remaining tomato mixture.'),
('27046', '4', 'Garnish, if desired.'),
('27046', '5', 'Note: For testing purposes only, we used Absolut Peppar Vodka and Tabasco Green Pepper Sauce.'),
('27046', '6', 'Kane''s Bloody Mary: Substitute regular vodka for pepper vodka. Proceed with recipe as directed.'),
('27047', '1', 'Cook scallions, jalapeno, bell pepper, and 1/2 teaspoon salt in butter in a 12-inch heavy skillet over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until scallions begin to brown, 7 to 9 minutes. Stir in tomatoes and cook, stirring occasionally, until broken down into a sauce, about 15 minutes.'),
('27047', '2', 'Add corn and okra and cook, stirring occasionally, until just tender, about 15 minutes.'),
('27051', '1', 'Prepare grill for cooking. If using a charcoal grill, open vents on bottom of grill, then light charcoal. Charcoal fire is medium-hot when you can hold your hand 5 inches above rack for 3 to 4 seconds. If using a gas grill, preheat burners on high, covered, 10 minutes, then reduce heat to moderate.'),
('27051', '2', 'Cut bread into 3/4-inch-thick slices (cut baguette on a long diagonal for 6-inch-long slices).'),
('27051', '3', 'Working in batches of 3 or 4 slices, grill bread on lightly oiled grill rack, covered only if using a gas grill, turning over once, until grill marks appear, 1 to 2 minutes total per batch.'),
('27051', '4', 'Remove bread from heat and immediately rub 1 side of each slice with cut side of a garlic half, then rub with cut side of a tomato half, using 1 tomato half for 1 to 2 slices of bread and allowing most of pulp to be absorbed by bread (discard remainder of garlic and tomato halves).'),
('27051', '5', 'Brush bread with oil, then sprinkle with salt and serve immediately.'),
('27055', '1', 'Watch how to make this recipe.'),
('27055', '2', 'Prepare a bowl with ice and water. Line a sheet pan with paper towels.'),
('27055', '3', 'In a 5-quart pot, bring 6 cups water to a boil over moderately-high heat. After the water has reached a boil, turn off the heat. Crack each egg into a ramekin and quickly add to the water. Once you have added all the eggs, cover the pot and set aside for 3 minutes.'),
('27055', '4', 'Using a slotted spoon, very carefully lift the eggs out of the water and directly into the bowl of ice water to stop the cooking.'),
('27055', '5', 'Remove from the ice water and place on the prepared sheet pan.'),
('27055', '6', 'Spread the flour on a plate and put the beaten eggs in a shallow bowl. In another shallow bowl, stir the panko with salt and pepper.'),
('27055', '7', 'Carefully dust 1 poached egg in the flour, dusting off any excess.'),
('27055', '8', 'Transfer the poached egg to the beaten eggs, and then transfer with a slotted spoon to the panko. Coat with the panko and carefully place on a plate. Repeat with the remaining eggs.'),
('27055', '9', 'Heat the oil in a heavy saucepan over high heat until a candy thermometer registers 350 degrees F. Using a slotted spoon, place 1 panko-coated egg into the oil and fry until golden brown, 10 to 15 seconds.'),
('27055', '10', 'Transfer the fried egg to paper towels to drain. Repeat with the remaining eggs.'),
('27055', '11', 'Season the tomato with salt and pepper.'),
('27055', '12', 'Place 1 tomato slice on each plate and top each slice with an egg.'),
('27055', '13', 'BYOC: Try this in early spring over some steamed asparagus. You can always add some fresh spinach to this for a crunch.'),
('27055', '14', 'Add the whole thing over a nice thick piece of crusty bread or English muffin for a fun brunch item.'),
('27056', '1', 'Hands On: 25 minutes Total: 25 minutes  Melt Fleischmann''s in medium saucepan over medium heat.'),
('27056', '2', 'Add onions. cook 2 to 3 minutes, or until onion softens, stirring occasionally.'),
('27056', '3', 'Add undrained tomatoes, broth, tomato paste and salt. mix well. Bring to a boil over medium heat. Reduce heat to low. simmer 5 to 10 minutes, or until slightly thickened, stirring occasionally.  Slowly add about 1/2 cup tomato mixture to cream. mix well. Gradually stir cream mixture into saucepan.'),
('27056', '4', 'Remove from heat.'),
('27056', '5', 'Pour into blender or food processor container and work in batches if necessary. cover. Pulse a few times, then blend just until smooth.'),
('27056', '6', 'Garnish each serving with sour cream or basil, if desired.'),
('27059', '1', 'Prepare barbecue (high heat), leaving opposite side unlit if gas grill or without coals if charcoal grill.'),
('27059', '2', 'Mix breadcrumbs and olive oil in small bowl, mashing to coat.'),
('27059', '3', 'Cut top 1/4 from each tomato. Sprinkle tomatoes with salt and pepper. Top each with 1 tablespoon blue cheese. Sprinkle with breadcrumb mixture.'),
('27059', '4', 'Arrange tomatoes (topping side up) on unlit side of grill. Cover grill and cook tomatoes until slightly soft and cheese melts, about 13 minutes.'),
('27059', '5', 'Serve immediately.'),
('27070', '1', 'Make soup: Warm olive oil in a large pan over medium-high heat.'),
('27070', '2', 'Add onion and cook, stirring, until softened, 5 minutes. Stir in thyme. cook 1 minute.'),
('27070', '3', 'Add tomatoes and broth. Bring to a simmer and cook, uncovered, until tomatoes are softened and soup is slightly thickened, 25 to 30 minutes. Season with salt and pepper.'),
('27070', '4', 'Remove from heat and cool slightly. Puree in a blender or food processor.'),
('27070', '5', 'Pour into a bowl, cover and chill at least 6 hours or overnight.'),
('27070', '6', 'Make croutons: Preheat broiler to high and set a rack about 8 inches from heat source.'),
('27070', '7', 'Brush both sides of bread with butter and place on a baking sheet. Broil, watching carefully to prevent burning, until golden brown, about 3 minutes per side.'),
('27070', '8', 'Rub each crouton with halved garlic while warm. Arrange 3 croutons on top of each bowl of soup or 1 crouton in a cup of soup, or serve alongside.'),
('27073', '1', 'Arrange tomatoes, cut side up, on rimmedbaking sheet. Sprinkle with salt and pepper,then 1 1/2 tablespoons each oregano andthyme leaves.'),
('27073', '2', 'Drizzle with 3 tablespoons oil.DO AHEAD: Can be made 2 hours ahead.'),
('27073', '3', 'Let stand at room temperature.'),
('27073', '4', 'Prepare barbecue (medium-high heat).'),
('27073', '5', 'Brush grill rack with oil.'),
('27073', '6', 'Place tomatoes,cut side up, on rack. Cook until bottoms arecharred, 3 to 4 minutes. Turn tomatoes overand grill just to sear, about 1 minute. Turncut side up onto platter. Sprinkle with 1/2tablespoon each oregano and thyme, thendrizzle with more oil, if desired.'),
('27073', '7', 'Serve warm.'),
('27078', '1', 'Watch how to make this recipe.'),
('27078', '2', 'In a deep-fryer, preheat oil to 350 degrees F.'),
('27078', '3', 'Season tomatoes, on both sides, with salt and pepper.'),
('27078', '4', 'Place flour and garlic powder in a shallow dish. In another shallow dish, beat eggs with the milk. In another dish, mix bread crumbs with cayenne and paprika. Dredge tomatoes through the flour, then the eggs, and then through the bread crumbs.'),
('27078', '5', 'Add only a few pieces to the fryer at a time, so they can cook evenly, about 2 to 3 minutes.'),
('27079', '1', 'Whisk together oil, vinegar, brown sugar, salt, and pepper in a small bowl. Arrange one third of tomatoes in 1 layer on a large plate, then drizzle with some dressing and sprinkle with some scallion. Make 2 more layers of tomatoes, drizzling each with dressing and sprinkling with scallion.'),
('27082', '1', 'Warm oil in a large saucepan over medium-high heat.'),
('27082', '2', 'Add garlic and cook, stirring, until fragrant, about 1 minute. Stir in tomatoes with their juice, sugar, Italian seasoning and cayenne and bring just to a boil. Puree in batches and chill in refrigerator or over a larger bowl of ice water. Season with salt.'),
('27082', '3', 'Ladle chilled soup into bowls. Top each portion with some shrimp and 1 tsp. pesto and serve.'),
('27087', '1', 'Puree onion in a blender or food processor along with enough tomatoes to yield about 4 cups of tomato puree.'),
('27087', '2', 'Pour puree into a 4- to 5-quart slow cooker along with broth, brown sugar, basil, Worcestershire, and cocoa powder. Cover and cook on Low 6 to 8 hours.'),
('27087', '3', 'Ten minutes before serving, stir in evaporated milk and butter. season with salt and pepper.'),
('27087', '4', 'Heat an additional 10 minutes, and serve.'),
('27088', '1', 'Cook onion in oil with spices in a 3-quart heavy saucepan over moderate heat, stirring occasionally, until onion is softened and begins to brown, 4 to 5 minutes. Coarsely chop tomatoes and add to onion mixture with reserved juices, broth, honey, 1 tablespoon parsley, and 1 tablespoon cilantro, then bring to a boil.'),
('27088', '2', 'Transfer soup to a metal bowl set in a larger bowl of ice and cold water. Cool soup, stirring occasionally, until cold, 15 to 20 minutes. Stir in lemon juice and salt and pepper to taste, then stir in remaining parsley and cilantro.'),
('27090', '1', 'Sprinkle tomatoes with salt and place, cut side down, on a paper towellined plate.'),
('27090', '2', 'Let stand 30 minutes to drain.'),
('27090', '3', 'Preheat oven to 425F. Mist a baking dish with cooking spray, then arrange tomato halves, cut side up, in a single layer in dish.'),
('27090', '4', 'In a small bowl, combine herbs, shallot and garlic.'),
('27090', '5', 'Add pepper, to taste.'),
('27090', '6', 'Spread herb mixture evenly over tomatoes.'),
('27090', '7', 'Drizzle with oil.'),
('27090', '8', 'Bake in oven until cooked through, about 20 minutes.'),
('27090', '9', 'Remove dish from oven, top with fresh basil and serve.'),
('27091', '1', 'Prepare barbecue (medium heat). Arrange eggplant slices on baking sheet.'),
('27091', '2', 'Brush both sides with oil and sprinkle with salt and pepper. Grill until slightly charred and tender, turning occasionally and moving to cook evenly, about 5 minutes.'),
('27091', '3', 'Transfer to foil-lined baking sheet. Grill plum tomato until skin is charred and split, turning often, about 5 minutes.'),
('27091', '4', 'Transfer to sheet with eggplant and cool. Core plum tomato. place in blender.'),
('27091', '5', 'Add chopped basil, vinegar, and 1/4 cup oil. Blend until smooth. Season with salt and pepper.'),
('27091', '6', 'Transfer to small bowl. DO AHEAD Eggplant and dressing can be made 2 hours ahead.'),
('27091', '7', 'Let stand at room temperature.'),
('27091', '8', 'Overlap eggplant slices, cheese slices, and heirloom tomato slices on individual plates or large platter. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.'),
('27091', '9', 'Drizzle salad with dressing and garnish with basil sprigs.'),
('27093', '1', 'Combine all ingredients in a small bowl.'),
('27093', '2', 'Serve at room temperature or chilled.'),
('27094', '1', 'Preheat oven to 20'),
('27094', '2', 'Cut tomatoes into 1/4-inch-thick slices. Sprinkle both sides of tomatoes evenly with salt and pepper.'),
('27094', '3', 'Pour buttermilk into a shallow dish or pie plate. Stir together cornmeal, Creole seasoning, and 1 cup flour in another shallow dish or pie plate.'),
('27094', '4', 'Dredge tomatoes in remaining 1 cup flour. Dip tomatoes in buttermilk, and dredge in cornmeal mixture.'),
('27094', '5', 'Pour oil to a depth of 2 inches in a large cast-iron skillet. heat over medium heat to 35'),
('27094', '6', 'Fry tomatoes, in batches, 2 to 3 minutes on each side or until golden.'),
('27094', '7', 'Drain on paper towels.'),
('27094', '8', 'Transfer to a wire rack. keep warm in a 200 oven until ready to serve. Sprinkle with salt to taste.'),
('27094', '9', 'Serve with Bread-and-Butter Pickle Rmoulade.'),
('27094', '10', 'Garnish, if desired.'),
('27098', '1', 'Preheat oven to 42'),
('27098', '2', 'Place tomato slices in a single layer on a baking sheet coated with cooking spray.'),
('27098', '3', 'Drizzle tomato slices evenly with 1 1/2 teaspoons oil. sprinkle evenly with 1/4 teaspoon salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.'),
('27098', '4', 'Bake at 425 for 15 to 17 minutes or until tomatoes begin to brown and skins wrinkle.'),
('27098', '5', 'While tomatoes bake, heat remaining 1/2 teaspoon oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat.'),
('27098', '6', 'Add garlic, and saut 1 minute.'),
('27098', '7', 'Add spinach, and cook 1 to 2 minutes or until spinach wilts. Stir in 1/8 teaspoon salt.'),
('27098', '8', 'Combine ricotta, goat cheese, and remaining 1/8 teaspoon pepper in a small bowl. microwave at HIGH 30 seconds to soften.'),
('27098', '9', 'Preheat broiler.'),
('27098', '10', 'Top bread slices evenly with half of tomatoes. top evenly with wilted spinach mixture. Spoon ricotta cheese mixture evenly over spinach. top evenly with remaining tomato slices. Sprinkle bruschetta evenly with Parmesan cheese.'),
('27098', '11', 'Place bruschetta on a baking sheet. broil 1 minute or until cheese melts.'),
('27101', '1', 'Combine first 5 ingredients in a large zip-top plastic freezer bag. add tomatoes, seal, and shake gently to coat. Chill 1 hour.'),
('27101', '2', 'Preheat grill to 350 to 400 (medium-high) heat.'),
('27101', '3', 'Remove tomatoes from marinade, reserving marinade. Grill tomatoes, covered with grill lid, 3 to 4 minutes on each side or until tender and grill marks appear.'),
('27101', '4', 'Arrange alternating slices of warm grilled tomatoes and mozzarella cheese on a large, shallow platter.'),
('27101', '5', 'Drizzle with reserved marinade. season with salt and pepper to taste. Sprinkle with basil.'),
('27106', '1', 'Make the Bloody Mary'),
('27106', '2', 'In a bowl, toss the celery with the onion, tomato, lemon zest and juice and season with salt. Refrigerate while you make the drinks.'),
('27106', '3', 'Make the Bloody Mary'),
('27106', '4', 'In a blender, puree the tomatoes, vodka, ice, tomato paste, chile and celery salt. pour into glasses. Spoon the garnish on top, add a celery rib and chile to each glass and serve.'),
('27110', '1', 'Heat your soup pot on medium-high. Separate your spices into three groups that can be added to the pot easily: mustard seeds, "wet" spices (the curry leaves, chile, and garlic), and the dry spices (reserving a teaspoon of the amchoor for later).'),
('27110', '2', 'Add the ghee or oil and let it heat till it shimmers and a cumin seed cracks instantly. Then add the mustard seeds and wait for them to pop.'),
('27110', '3', 'When the mustard seeds are popping everywhere, add the wet spices and stir to coat with oil. A few seconds later, add the dry spices, and stir to coat again. When the pot is intensely aromatic, add the tomatoes. It''s important to do this quickly, so the spices get just toasted, but don''t start to burn.'),
('27110', '4', 'Bring the soup to a boil, then reduce to a moderate simmer.'),
('27110', '5', 'Let it cook for about 20 to 30 minutes, tasting often to add seasoning, any necessary sugar (which can make a huge difference in tomato dishes), and any additional water (I added about 2 cups towards the end of simmering). The broth should be quite thin but still flavorful. After 20 to 30 minutes, the spices should have married well together. Shortly before serving, stir in the remaining amchoor.'),
('27110', '6', 'Garnish with cilantro and serve as an appetizer or as a dipping broth for fritters.'),
('27114', '1', 'Place the tomatoes, red pepper, onions and garlic on a baking pan with the cut sides up.'),
('27114', '2', 'Drizzle a bit of olive oil over everything and season with salt and pepper.Roast in a 375F preheated oven for 45 minutes.'),
('27114', '3', 'Place everything but the cream into a sauce pan and simmer for 15 minutes.Puree with a hand blender to desired consistency and mix in the cream.'),
('27115', '1', 'Bring everything but the tomatoes to a boil for 3 minutes.'),
('27115', '2', 'Meanwhile, stuff the tomatoes in the the jar(s).'),
('27115', '3', 'Pour the liquid over the tomatoes making sure to cover them.'),
('27115', '4', 'Put the lids on and give them a good shake to make that all of the air bubbles come out to the top.'),
('27119', '1', 'Saute onion and celery in olive oil in a Dutch oven over medium heat. When  onion is translucent (about 7 minutes), add the tomatoes, broth, oregano, basil, and cayenne. Bring to a boil, then simmer on low heat for 10 minutes.'),
('27119', '2', 'Transfer half of the soup to the blender, add the roasted garlic, and puree until fairly smooth. If you''d like a chunky soup, add the blended half back to the pot. For a smoother soup, blend the rest of the soup and return it to the pot.'),
('27119', '3', 'Add the parsley and salt and pepper to taste, and simmer for about 10 minutes to allow the flavors to blend. Taste the soup, and if it is too acidic, add sugar, just enough to take the edge off. If desired, serve with croutons or a tablespoon of yogurt stirred into each bowl.'),
('27129', '1', 'In a large bowl, toss the chopped tomatoes with the cucumbers, tomato juice, olive oil, lemon juice, onion and 3 tablespoons each of the basil and cilantro. Working in batches, puree the vegetables in a blender.'),
('27129', '2', 'Pour the soup into another large bowl, season with salt and pepper and refrigerate until chilled.'),
('27129', '3', 'Meanwhile, in a small bowl, blend the goat cheese with the remaining 2 tablespoons each of basil and cilantro and season with salt and pepper.'),
('27129', '4', 'In a small saucepan of boiling salted water, cook the sugar snaps until just tender, about 1 minute.'),
('27129', '5', 'Drain and refresh under cold water, then pat dry and halve.'),
('27129', '6', 'Ladle the soup into shallow bowls and spoon a dollop of herbed goat cheese into the center of each.'),
('27129', '7', 'Garnish with the sugar snaps, cherry tomatoes, radishes and avocado and serve.'),
('27130', '1', 'Drain 1 can tomatoes, discarding juice, then puree with remaining can tomatoes (including juice) in a blender.'),
('27130', '2', 'Cook onion, garlic, chile, and ginger in oil in a 4- to 5-quart heavy nonreactive pot over moderate heat, stirring frequently, until onion is softened, about 8 minutes.'),
('27130', '3', 'Add cumin and cook, stirring, 1 minute. Stir in pureed tomatoes, broth, 1 tablespoon sugar, and 2 teaspoons salt and simmer, uncovered, stirring occasionally, 20 minutes. Working in 3 or 4 batches, blend soup in blender until smooth (use caution when blending hot liquids).'),
('27130', '4', 'Transfer soup as blended to a sieve set over a large bowl and force through sieve, discarding seeds.'),
('27130', '5', 'Stir in sugar and salt to taste. Reheat in cleaned saucepan if necessary.'),
('27131', '1', 'Place the tomatoes on a baking sheet with the cut side facing up.'),
('27131', '2', 'Sprinkle with the garlic, salt and pepper and drizzle with oil and vinegar.'),
('27131', '3', 'Roast the tomatoes in a preheated 350F oven for an hour.'),
('27131', '4', 'Let the tomatoes cool, assemble the salad and enjoy.'),
('27132', '1', 'Prepare barbecue (high heat).'),
('27132', '2', 'Brush grill rack with oil.'),
('27132', '3', 'Brush pattypan squash, zucchini, and tomatoes with olive oil. sprinkle generously with salt and pepper. Grill until vegetables are blistered and slightly charred, about 8 minutes for squash and zucchini, turning occasionally, and about 6 minutes for tomatoes, shifting occasionally.'),
('27132', '4', 'Transfer to platter.'),
('27140', '1', 'Cut 1 round from each bread slice with cookie cutter.'),
('27140', '2', 'Cook bacon in a 10-inch heavy skillet over moderate heat until crisp, then transfer to paper towels to drain.'),
('27140', '3', 'Pour off bacon fat from skillet and reserve fat (do not clean skillet).'),
('27140', '4', 'Heat 1 1/2 tablespoons oil in skillet over moderate heat until hot but not smoking, then toast 3 bread rounds, turning over once, until golden brown, about 3 minutes total.'),
('27140', '5', 'Transfer toasts to a rack to cool and season with salt and pepper. Toast remaining 3 bread rounds in 1 1/2 tablespoons more oil in same manner.'),
('27140', '6', 'Cook shallot in 2 tablespoons reserved bacon fat and remaining 3 tablespoons oil in a small heavy saucepan over moderate heat, stirring, until softened, about 2 minutes.'),
('27140', '7', 'Add vinegar and simmer, whisking, until emulsified, about 1 minute. Season dressing with salt and pepper and keep warm, covered.'),
('27140', '8', 'Crumble bacon. Arrange bread rounds on 6 plates and divide tomato slices among them, stacking slices and sprinkling some basil and bacon between slices. Sprinkle cheese and remaining basil and bacon over and around tomatoes. Spoon some of warm bacon dressing over and around tomatoes and season with salt and pepper.'),
('27142', '1', 'Preheat the oven to 425 degrees Fahrenheit.Layer tomatoes in the bottom of a cast-iron or enameled cast-iron skillet, sprinkle with minced shallot, fresh herbs, unrefined sea salt and ground black pepper.'),
('27142', '2', 'Drizzle with olive oil and bake in an oven preheated to 425 degrees Fahrenheit for ten to fifteen minutes.'),
('27150', '1', 'Cook beans, covered, in a large pot of lightly salted boiling water over high heat 10 minutes or until crisp-tender.'),
('27150', '2', 'Place dill and next 3 ingredients in a large heatproof glass bowl.'),
('27150', '3', 'Drain beans well, and add to dill mixture.'),
('27150', '4', 'Add olive oil, and toss well.'),
('27150', '5', 'Add tomato and onion, and toss gently. Cover and refrigerate up to 24 hours.'),
('27150', '6', 'Remove beans from refrigerator, and let stand, covered, at room temperature 1 hour.'),
('27150', '7', 'Add 2 tablespoons lemon juice, and toss gently. Taste for seasoning, and add remaining lemon juice, if desired.'),
('27152', '1', 'Preheat the oven to 375 degrees F. In a food processor, pulse the cheeses and butter into small pieces. Pulse in the flour until it resembles coarse sand, then turn into a large bowl.'),
('27152', '2', 'Add cream, if necessary, until the dough forms a solid ball when pressed together. In a food processor, pulse the hazelnuts and 1 cup Cocoa Krispies until fine.'),
('27152', '3', 'Roll the dough out on a floured surface to 1/2-inch thick and evenly press the Cocoa Krispies-hazelnut mixture onto the dough.'),
('27152', '4', 'Cut the dough into 24 pieces and bake on a buttered baking pan until golden brown, about 15 minutes. While the cookies are baking, start the tomato soup.'),
('27152', '5', 'Heat the olive oil in a large saucepan and cook the shallot and garlic until soft but not brown.'),
('27152', '6', 'Add the tomatoes and cook over medium heat for about 10 minutes.'),
('27152', '7', 'Add the wine and stock and simmer 7 minutes more.'),
('27152', '8', 'Add the remaining 1 cup Cocoa Krispies and cook for another 3 minutes. Puree the soup in a blender until smooth and season with salt and pepper.'),
('27152', '9', 'Serve the tomato soup with the cookies on the side for dipping.'),
('27159', '1', 'Salt the tomatoes, then, in a mixer fitted with a paddle, and crush them.'),
('27159', '2', 'Let sit for two hours to allow for the greatest extraction of juice.'),
('27159', '3', 'In the meantime, combine the remaining ingredients and puree until smooth and almost liquid.'),
('27159', '4', 'Add to macerating tomatoes.'),
('27159', '5', 'Pass the tomato mixture through a food mill or sieve. Taste and adjust seasonings. Refrigerate.'),
('27159', '6', 'Serve over ice in tall chilled highball glasses.'),
('27159', '7', 'Add vodka if desired.'),
('27159', '8', 'Garnish with a stick of cumber or celery.'),
('27162', '1', 'Heat the oil in a large, deep saucepan over low heat.'),
('27162', '2', 'Saute the garlic until just fragrant, then add the bread, stirring until all the oil is absorbed and the bread is toasted.'),
('27162', '3', 'Add the tomatoes, stock, basil, and salt.'),
('27162', '4', 'Bring to a boil, then reduce heat. Simmer until the bread breaks down, about 20 minutes.'),
('27162', '5', 'Remove the garlic and serve.'),
('27181', '1', 'Preheat oven to 350F.'),
('27181', '2', 'Arrange tomatoes, cut sides up, in a shallow baking dish just large enough to hold them in 1 layer.'),
('27181', '3', 'Drizzle with 2 tablespoons oil and season with salt and pepper. Scatter garlic around tomatoes, then roast in middle of oven until tomatoes are tender and skins are wrinkled, about 1 hour. Cool, then transfer tomatoes to a plate, reserving garlic and oil in baking dish.'),
('27181', '4', 'While tomatoes are cooling, put bread slices on a baking sheet and brush lightly on both sides with additional oil.'),
('27181', '5', 'Bake in middle of oven until golden, 15 to 18 minutes.'),
('27181', '6', 'Peel roasted garlic cloves and mash to a paste with oil and juices from baking dish.'),
('27181', '7', 'Spread paste on toasts, then top each toast with a tomato half, cut side up.'),
('27181', '8', 'Serve crostini topped with mint and olives.'),
('27183', '1', 'In a large saucepan, melt 1 tablespoon of the butter in 1 tablespoon of the olive oil.'),
('27183', '2', 'Add the sliced onion and smashed garlic and cook over moderate heat, stirring occasionally, until softened, about 5 minutes.'),
('27183', '3', 'Add the tomatoes and their juice, the water, heavy cream, sugar, crushed red pepper, celery seed and oregano and season with salt and pepper. Bring the soup to a boil over high heat, breaking up the tomatoes with the back of a spoon. Reduce the heat to moderate and simmer for 10 minutes.'),
('27183', '4', 'Meanwhile, in a small skillet, cook the remaining 1 tablespoon of butter over moderately high heat until it begins to brown, about 1 minute. Scrape the browned butter into a medium bowl.'),
('27183', '5', 'Add the olive oil to the skillet.'),
('27183', '6', 'Add the diced bread and cook over moderately high heat, stirring occasionally, until it is slightly browned, about 6 minutes.'),
('27183', '7', 'Transfer the bread to the browned butter and toss well.'),
('27183', '8', 'Working in batches, transfer the tomato soup to a blender and puree until smooth. Return the soup to a clean pot and rewarm the soup if necessary. Season the soup with salt and pepper. Ladle the soup into bowls and serve with the croutons.'),
('27188', '1', 'Preheat oven to 425F.'),
('27188', '2', 'Whisk flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and baking soda in large bowl to blend. Using fingertips, rub 3/4 cup chilled butter into dry ingredients until mixture resembles coarse meal. Stir in chives.'),
('27188', '3', 'Add buttermilk and stir until evenly moistened. Using 1/4 cup dough for each biscuit, drop biscuits onto baking sheet, spacing 2 inches apart.*'),
('27188', '4', 'Bake until biscuits are golden brown on top, about 15 minutes. Cool slightly.'),
('27188', '5', 'Serve warm.* Im a sucker for the round, bumpy-edged biscuit shape so I rolled it out on well-floured counter and cut them with a 3 biscuit-cutter. Take care to handle the dough as little as humanly possible, so not to warm or soften it too much.See more: Breakfast, Drinks, Eggs, Mushrooms, Photo, Scones/Biscuits, Spinach'),
('27188', '6', 'Do more: Link | Bookmark| Pin | Print| Email| 103 Comments'),
('27194', '1', 'Position an oven rack in the center of the oven and preheat the oven to 375F. Line a baking sheet with parchment paper.'),
('27194', '2', 'Core and slice the tomatoes into 1/8- to -inch-thick rounds, discarding the end slices. (The tomatoes should be cut on the thin side so their juices can evaporate during baking before they have a chance to make the crust soggy.)'),
('27194', '3', 'Place the tomato rounds on paper towels. Cover with another layer of paper towels and let stand to drain excess juices while preparing the phyllo crust.'),
('27194', '4', 'Place a phyllo sheet on the baking sheet.'),
('27194', '5', 'Brush the phyllo with olive oil. Top with the remaining phyllo sheets, brushing each with oil. Fold over the four sides of the phyllo stack to make a 1-inch-wide border. Sprinkle the area inside the border with the Parmesan. Top with the tomato slices, overlapping the slices as needed. Sprinkle with the goat cheese and season with salt and pepper to taste.');